Overview of adv ill

The adv ill has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                             
1. (3) ill, badly, poorly -- ((`ill' is often used as a combining form) in a poor or improper or unsatisfactory manner; not well; "he was ill prepared"; "it ill befits a man to betray old friends"; "the car runs badly"; "he performed badly on the exam"; "the team played poorly"; "ill-fitting clothes"; "an ill-conceived plan")
2. ill, badly -- (unfavorably or with disapproval; "tried not to speak ill of the dead"; "thought badly of him for his lack of concern")
3. ill -- (with difficulty or inconvenience; scarcely or hardly; "we can ill afford to buy a new car just now")
